column1: Align Pant Super High-Rise Online Only 28"
column6:
So, I'm 100% convinced that there was a fabric update. My new Align pants are texturally different than my older pairs. My newer pairs don't get the layer of fuzz all over, like the older pairs. However, they do get the crotch pilling, like every other tight that isn't luxtreme. I periodically use a sweater shaver and I'm good to go. At any rate, onto my review of the Super High-Rise Align. I LOVE THESE TIGHTS! They are buttery soft and the higher rise waistband goes up and over my really high belly button, without making my crotch look long. I purchased the Melanite color, which is a welcome change from basic black while still being just as versatile. That said, I'll be buying the black pair as well.
These are the perfect tights for yoga. The extended gusset provides freedom of movement, without any seams digging in. I never worry about these tights being see through in a forward fold or straddle.
Please keep in mind when purchasing these tights that they are specifically a YOGA tight (although they are great to hang out it as well). If you're looking for a more versatile tight (for other workouts), buy the Wunder Unders.

column1: Align Pant Super High-Rise Online Only 28"

column1: Align Pant Super High-Rise Online Only 28"
column6: I went into a lululemon store for the first time in my life yesterday. I was very hungover. I grabbed 6 pairs of leggings and went to the dressing room. When I was in the dressing room I was overheating and trying not to throw up. But I am a tough girl so I didn't give up and tried the leggings on.Everyone says they are amazing and let me tell you the hype is real. Head was pounding, room was spinning but my butt looked amazing. Even though I was feeling awful I felt like I could do 30 hours of yoga. Everyone says they are amazing and let me tell you the hype is real. So I leave the dressing room knowing that I'm about to make a horrible decision financially, but an amazing decision for my overall well being. I buy 3 pairs of leggings, yep that's right, the most hungover decision of all time? maybe. I get home still feeling awful I take a shower, after the shower I still felt awful (which is always my cure), but then I put on the leggings... I swear I felt so much better. The world wasn't spinning, my head wasn't pounding, and for the first time in my life my flat butt looked like a hill instead of a valley! I LOVE THEM. I am very GRATEFUL that hungover me made a "bad" decision, because it turned out to be one of the best decisions I have ever made. Glad I bought 3 because I will be wearing these for the rest of my lil life. When I get married? probably. When I go to the beach? you bet. When I go to the nursing home in 60 years? heck yes! Thanks lulu. You da best!

column6: My husband likes to say that I look like a granny while wearing anything high waisted, and I say back that the higher the waist, the closer to God. I guess if you wanted to you could also roll the waist, but that’s not my jam, lets hold my gut in! As for the fabric, I’m absolutely in love with the Align line. These are buttery soft and just the right amount of compression. Anything too tight triggers my anxiety and these are the perfect fit. The only downside is that I’m 5’3” so the length is too long. The 21” inseam is perfect for me so after I purchased them online I took them to a store and had them sent in for hemming (pssst it’s free!). So I wish they offered more lengths for the super high-rise, but that’s the only complaint. I guess they could also add more colors!

column1: Align Pant Super High-Rise Online Only 28"
column6: i wish i bought these pants while pregnant, to wear during the first days and weeks postpartum. they provide the right kind of support without suffocating me &/or cutting off my circulation. i am 5 months postpartum and almost back at pre-pregnancy weight, so i bought 1 size up from my pre-pregnancy size. i wear these constantly, i'm considering buying a 2nd pair. i do agree with other reviewers that the fabric is very delicate and at risk of piling. i cannot just toss these in the wash with my other clothes. i turned them inside out, wash with other similar clothes that do not have buttons or zippers, etc, on the gentlest setting. i still expect them some piling because i feel the fabric kind of catching every time i sit on a couch with rougher fabric. if pilling is a major concern for you, don't get these pants -- find pants made of a more durable fabric.

column1: Align Pant Super High-Rise Online Only 28"
column5: Extra High Rise are so good!
column6: Disclaimer, I owned 8 pairs of align pants before the Extra High Rise came out. I'm currently 6 month pregnant and these are the pants I'm always turning to. They were one of my favorite Lulu styles but these are so easy to transition into pregnancy, the extra high rise was a no brainer and I'm so glad I got them. They are more comfortable than any other maternity leggings I've tried and I know they are going to be in my top favorites once me back heals. The only downside is that if the other aligns are any indication they will pill and that sucks. I wouldn't recommend them for high intensity workouts.
